25|$|On January 16, 2003, protests {{were held}} {{worldwide}} {{in opposition to}} <b>a</b> <b>war</b> <b>with</b> <b>Iraq,</b> including in Turkey, Egypt, Pakistan, Japan, Belgium, the Netherlands, Argentina, and the United States, where Americans attended a rally in Washington, D.C. The U.S. Park Police, which oversees activities on the National Mall, stopped providing estimates of crowd size after being threatened with lawsuits by {{the organizers of the}} Million Man March, but said that protest organizers only had a permit for 30,000 demonstrators.|$|E
