2500|$|After the U.S. Congress {{prohibited}} {{federal funding}} of the Contras through the Boland Amendment in 1983, the Reagan administration continued to back the Contras by raising money from foreign allies and covertly selling arms to Iran (then engaged in <b>a</b> <b>war</b> <b>with</b> <b>Iraq),</b> and channelling the proceeds to the Contras (see the Iran–Contra affair). When this scheme was revealed, Reagan admitted that he knew about Iranian [...] "arms for hostages" [...] dealings but professed ignorance about the proceeds funding the Contras; for this, National Security Council aide Lt. Col. Oliver North took much of the blame.|$|E
