50|$|The {{co-operation}} between Bull and Saddam Hussein was {{an immediate}} threat to Iran and Israel, as Iran had endured <b>an</b> eight-year-long <b>war</b> <b>with</b> <b>Iraq,</b> and Israel had previous military engagements <b>with</b> <b>Iraq</b> during the Arab-Israeli war. Watching development of the gun, Israel feared {{it could be used}} to launch nuclear weapons, but the re-designed SCUD missiles were of greater concern at that moment. As for Iran, it was under threat from both Bull's supergun and his re-designed SCUD missiles.|$|R
